OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: vg
Version: 0.0.1
Synopsis: Declarative 2D vector graphics for OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2013 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/vg
Description:
 Vg is an OCaml module for declarative 2D vector graphics. It has a precise
 denotational semantics and an open backend. Built-in support for PDF, SVG 
 and HTML5 2D canvas output is provided.
 .
 Vg is made of a single module, depends on [Gg][1] and is distributed under 
 the BSD3 license.
 .
 [1]: http://erratique.ch/software/gg

